This has been the worst thanksgiving ever, I got sick grrr had to leave the family function cuz my stomach was getting all the worse, and as soon as I walked in my door and got to my bathroom (i was running lol) I was vomiting, grrr

Now I feel somewhat better, I hurt all over, im very tired, my stomach is still a lil tender but I just managed to eat a piece of turkey, first thing i have had all day long! Hope it stays down lol.  Even worse is that I gotta be in at work at 12 am fun fun for all to be had.

I felt like writing something but I have nothing to talk about cuz my life is boring and uneventful! :-P So off to work I go...

Ok...

Today I went to dads, family dinner thing and we gave him a gift that my sister made for him with our hand prints, basically we reverted back to kindergarten finger painting classes it rocked LOL.  So yeah, after that of course we got paint all over our hands so yes, you wash up! We wash up and of course dry your hands! Ah, here comes the twisted part of the story....


Being the only towel in the bathroom at the time we all use it to dry our hands...About 40 minutes pass from that and my step mother who is a clean freak, goes into the bathroom and collects the towel to put in the wash, she remarks to my step sister about it being wet and having visible stains and asks her if her husband "used" it, she nods in agreement and then my face goes into shock mode! So I ask her is she sure, she said yes she felt it and saw stains so I freak out and tell her we all used it earlier to dry our hands LOL ( if you dont get it now, the man cummed on the towel in the bathroom, ok the man should have done it in the shower or at least in the sink and wash it out!) Yeah so now I gotta get my baby sister to come wash her hands really well without being totally honest with her about WHY she had to wash her hands, now she is like  13 or 14 (im bad with ages, yeah bad big bro) still a lil sheltered, so we couldn't come right out and say hey Joe decided he needed a wank and used the towel that you dried your hands on as his cum towel, and then decided to return it like nothing ever happened! But we handled that pretty well but anyways...I never met Joe so I was violated by a man I never met! LOL Though I joked with my oldest sister about it, we basically both shared in the jizz of a man! Once in a life time experience I so hope! LOL 

Yeah that was my day...

Ask me about my day...
Seriously, ask me about my effin day!


lol

Today is so beautiful outside, the air is cool, a slight breeze it normally rocks but it also reminds me of him.  It makes me long for him and the good times.  I don't know if another guy will ever make me feel that way again, I sure hope so.  A boy can dream...

Just got in from a family function, it was nice, low key the way I like things sometimes hehe.  What stood out the most for me was my lil cousin Lauren, she has always been so shy around me but this time she was so friendly and wanted me to play with her and pull her around in her grandfathers garden cart it was fun!  I honestly cant wait for my nephew to be that age and wanna play and have fun it will rock!  And her sister is sweet too always funny and always has a story to tell you about something.  Now I can't wait for the next family function hehehe...

I had an unique experience, I was manning the sidewalk today for the sale (as I always do cuz I love being outside, and I get to check out all the cute bois LOL) and who walks by with his best friend? JON! omg It was weird, he winked and smiled at me and waved and I smirked and waved back and said hey, first time we have made any sort of communication with each other since the break up, except for his email that hurt/pissed me off. It made me miss him, that sucks Cuz I don't want to miss him, but I do. But I don't think it could work out again, as lonely as I am, I can't hurt again. Then there is Brian, I miss him too, I think I miss the sex tho LOL, it was hot! He moved back to NC in April, and I think he moved back to MN cuz I wouldn't take him back. Honestly, if he had paid me and dad back, and apologized to my family I probably would have taken him back, I know against what all of my friends and family suggested I do, but the heart wants what the heart wants, am I right? YES. But I think my heart was clouded with with the fact that the sex was HOTT! And I miss being with a guy that actually is as wild as I am in the bed. Hmm I'm seriously tired of alot of things here and feel I need a change. I know what one of you is probably thinking, maybe two of you :-P. On another subject, my desktop! Its dying, the hard drive wotn boot alot of the time now, I finally got it up and running an hour ago, after I opened it up and fidgetd with all the connections and blew it (get your minds out of the gutters) it was so dusty, I had a thought that maybe the dust was causing the problems, I don't know only time will tell. Anyway its a perfect excuse for me to get a new computer, maybe a Mac (yeah Will so I can read your away msgs that only you mac users can read, its not fair! :-P) or a Media Edition XP PC for my future home theater. I dunno tough decision, but I wont be buying a new computer for another three or so months, if this one holds out maybe a bit longer. Oh well, thats it im bored now, and need to get ready for bed, at least I can sleep in a lil bit before having to be at work, since I was at work at 730 this morning gawd don't know why, me being the hyper over achiever I can be sometimes LOL...

And check out that cute guy that works there LOL I always have an excuse to find cute bois hehe. Well I'm going to finish up my Dead Like Me DVD's and then hit the sheets. I feel a change of life heading my way...and I hope its for the best :-)

I have been so lonely today. I don't know why, maybe its just the mood thing and will pass, I sure hope so. But everything that has happened this weekend with Haden being born, made me realize that I had no one special beside me to share the news with. For some reason I expected Jon and I to still be together now, then he fucked up and we aren't. Why do I keep getting selfish guys? Or is it just me? Im starting to think its me. Saturday I was so excited and this thought popped into my head...Justin would be so excited to hear that I'm an uncle. I am excited and happy he is here don't get me wrong. But this has brought out all those feelings I must have pushed aside in order to focus on heather and the baby.  Its sad to say I'm used to being alone, but it hurts terribly. Maybe a nice guy will cross my path soon one can hope :-) and hopefully tomorrow will be a better day.
